Identity & Entity Nexus (IDN)
Documentation Master Plan (Aligned to NS-GGP Canonical Template)
PurposeThis document defines the authoritative documentation master plan for IDN, strictly aligned to the existing NS-GGP document structure (000–014).
IDN is the identity resolution, entity graph, and trust anchor engine for Northfield Solidarity. It provides a canonical way to represent people, services, agents, organizations, and external accounts, and to reason about their relationships. IDN does not make business decisions (GGP), execute actions (DAT), or generate insights (PIE).

IDN Documentation Index (Canonical)

NS-IDN-000 — CHARTER
Purpose: Define why IDN exists
Scope:
Mission of IDN
Why identity and entity resolution must be centralized
IDN’s role as a trust anchor across engines
Explicit non-goals (business logic, execution, scoring)
Mirrors: NS-GGP-000

NS-IDN-001 — OVERVIEW
Purpose: High-level conceptual framing
Scope:
What IDN represents (entities, identities, relationships)
How IDN supports governance, audit, and execution
Downstream consumers: GGP, DAT, FLO, MUX, SIM
Mirrors: NS-GGP-001

